ed to call public behavior asserts to create an adapter that shows missing functions ignored for compatibility, though most functions are supported.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering JavaScript object prototypes**\\n\\nI'm exploring how to set a parent or prototype for an empty object using JavaScript object literals. It seems like it could have a parent scope and the default `Object.prototype`. As an alternative, I might create a basic `NativeObject` in Java, which has no functions. Then I wonder how to retrieve `adapterClass` through `public JavaAdapter`. There’s quite a bit to consider when mixing these concepts!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_fSb34oZXyJHrp8fGwGX7t7ia|fc_01fc0e625fba6484016a2736953f1c81908ebc001ec2bc9221", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.mozilla/rhino/1.7R5/gradle.properties"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 567, "output": 2103, "cacheRead": 26624, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 29294, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780954725544, "responseId": "resp_01fc0e625fba6484016a2736662ba48190ba4bbfbfc2259b3b"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_fSb34oZXyJHrp8fGwGX7t7ia|fc_01fc0e625fba6484016a2736953f1c81908ebc001ec2bc9221", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Optional explicit tested library coordinates (format: group:artifact:version).\n# If omitted, fallback resolution in org.graalvm.internal.tck.gradle still uses\n# environment variable GVM_TCK_LC and then this property.\nlibrary.coordinates = org.mozilla:rhino:1.7R5\nlibrary.version = 1.7R5\nmetadata.dir = org.mozilla/rhino/1.7R5/\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1780954773766}]}
