[assistant] Updated `JavaAdapterTest` to fix the `ClassCache.get` top-level scope failure.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Changes in:
[assistant] 
[assistant] `tests/src/org.mozilla/rhino/1.7R5/src/test/java/org_mozilla/rhino/JavaAdapterTest.java`
[assistant] 
[assistant] What changed:
[assistant] - The `NativeObject` implementation is now attached to the Rhino top-level scope before calling `new JavaAdapter(...)`:
[assistant]   - `implementation.setParentScope(scope)`
[assistant]   - `implementation.setPrototype(ScriptableObject.getObjectPrototype(scope))`
[assistant] - After adapter creation and invocation, the implementation object is detached before serialization:
[assistant]   - `implementation.setParentScope(null)`
[assistant]   - `implementation.setPrototype(null)`
[assistant] 
[assistant] This keeps adapter creation on the supported Rhino path while avoiding serialization of the full top-level scope that previously led to `NotSerializableException`.
[assistant-event] text_end
